>
  <p>
    Installing a septic system isn't a single task — it's a sequence of stages, each building on the
    last. Understanding that sequence does two things for you: it sets realistic expectations for
    timing and budget, and it explains why a firm price can't come before the very first stage is
    done. Above all, it shows why the soil evaluation, not the shovel, is where every installation
    truly begins.
  </p>

  {/* Intended asset: /images/resources/the-septic-installation-process-hero.webp — see public/images/resources/README.md */}
